                    At Moscow and Nanking.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d507</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">507</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-14T07:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-14T07:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-14T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-14T07:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Korea)/5–1446: Circular
                    telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="94" xml:id="d507fn1">At Moscow and Nanking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-14T08:00:00-04:00">May 14, 1946—8 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On leaving Seoul with USSR deleg May 9 Gen Shtikov remarked he had not
                    communicated with Moscow on decision withdraw from Joint Commission
                    meetings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
